<!-- ABOUT DROUGHT -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>About Droughts</h2>
  <p>
    A drought is a long period of abnormally low rainfall that leads to water shortage.
    It affects drinking water, agriculture, livestock, and the overall environment.
  </p>
  <p>
    Droughts are common in Maharashtra, Rajasthan, Karnataka, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, and parts of MP.
  </p>
</article>

<!-- CAUSES -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Causes of Drought</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Low or delayed monsoon rainfall.</li>
    <li>High temperatures causing evaporation.</li>
    <li>Overuse of groundwater and rivers.</li>
    <li>Climate change and global warming.</li>
    <li>Poor water management.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- WARNING SIGNS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Warning Signs of Drought</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Dry lakes, rivers, ponds, and wells.</li>
    <li>Crop failure and dry soil.</li>
    <li>Reduced drinking water supply.</li>
    <li>Increase in dust storms.</li>
    <li>Livestock becoming weak due to lack of fodder.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- PREPAREDNESS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Preparedness Before/ During a Drought</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Store enough drinking water in clean containers.</li>
    <li>Use water only when necessary.</li>
    <li>Fix leaking taps and pipes.</li>
    <li>Use buckets instead of showers.</li>
    <li>Collect and reuse wastewater when possible.</li>
    <li>Grow drought-resistant crops in farming areas.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- DOs & DON'Ts -->
